, C.P., Ackerman, T.P., Santhaman, K., Rapid calculation of radiative heating and photodissociation rates in inhomogeneous multiple scattering atmospheres (1989) J. Geophys. Res., 94, pp. 16287-16301; (1996) Fourth Global Energy and Water Experiment (GEWEX) Cloud System Studies (GCSS) Boundary Layer Cloud Workshop, , http://www.phys.uu.nl/~wwwimau/old/ASTEX/astexcomp.html, 12-16 August, Clermont-Ferrand, France; Stevens, B., Evaluation of large-eddy simulations via observations of nocturnal marine stratocumulus (2003) Mon. Weath. Rev., , http://www.atmos.ucla.edu/~bstevens/dycoms/dycoms.html, (in the press); Eighth GCSS Boundary Layer Cloud Workshop. (29-31 October, Broomfield, Colorado, USA); Duynkerke, P.G., Observations and numerical simulations of the diurnal cycle of the EUROCS stratocumulus case (2002) Q. J. R. Meteorol. Soc., , http://www.phys.uu.nl/~wwwimau/research/atm_dyn/EUROCS_PART_I/eurocs.html, (in the press); European Project on Cloud Systems in Climate Models. (16-19 December, Madrid, Spain)","Ackerman, A.S.; NASA Ames Research Center, Moffett Field, CA 94035, United States; email: andrew.ackerman@nasa.gov",,,,,,,,00280836,,NATUA,,"English","Nature",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-11144232674
